Source: duckbotos-cua-bridge
Section: ai
Priority: optional
Maintainer: DuckBotOS Team <duckets@duckbotos.dev>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13)
Standards-Version: 4.6.2

Package: duckbotos-cua-bridge
Architecture: amd64 arm64
Depends: python3.12, python3-pip, git, curl, ca-certificates,
         duckbotos-computer-use,
         ${misc:Depends}
Description: DuckBotOS — trycua/cua bridge for VM orchestration + computer-use backend
 Installs the trycua/cua bridge used by DuckBotOS for two purposes:
 .
   1. **Sandbox layer** — programmatically spin up Linux/macOS/Windows
      VMs and containers for test runtimes, agent sandboxes, and the
      DuckBotOS build pipeline. Python SDK: `pip install cua`. Same API
      regardless of OS or runtime.
 .
   2. **Computer-use backend** — `cua-driver` runs as an MCP stdio server
      for desktop control, complementing the local Newest Desktop Control
      (Lobster Edition). Already tested with OpenClaw; Linux backend is
      pre-release (matches DuckBotOS's needs).
 .
 Setup:
   • Install: pip install cua cua-driver
   • Hermes:  claude mcp add --transport stdio cua-driver -- cua-driver mcp
   • OpenClaw: cua-driver plugin registered in openclaw.json via postinst
 .
 Reference: https://github.com/trycua/cua
 .
 This package is OPTIONAL — DuckBotOS works fine without it. Install to
 enable programmatic VM orchestration + add cua as a second computer-use
 backend alongside Newest Desktop Control.
